caption: I’ve only ever been for brunch, so that’s what I’ll be speaking on. Listen...three words...GET THE GRITS! None of the food on the brunch buffet disappointed, but don’t skip the grits! The only reason for four stars and not five is that the server struggled a bit keeping up with the drink orders.  everything was excellent, thank you

I was given a meal on the house - I had steak, tuna crudo, and tried the caprese flatbread. I also got the blueberry mule. These items were highly recommended by my waiter and they did not disappoint! The mule was one of the most delicious cocktails I've ever had. overall this place is good for me
Been to three other Blackwall Hitch this one is the least favorite of the three. Mashed potatoes had no flavor,  food was just warm.
Delicious food and drinks. Great service from Wolfgang.

All of the staff were so friendly, and inviting. The soup was barely warm, but the person who ordered it didn't mind. When my entree was served the masked potatoes and asparagus were ICE COLD, but the fish was fresh and hot. Our server IMMEDIATELY took care of it. The manager came to our table, with the corrected dish, apologized, and gave me a free beer. The entree was delicious!  In lieu of the cold dishes, I will definitely return. It was very good.

Covid compliant. Our waitress was nice. Service was fast. This was my first time visiting and will be the first and the last time I’ll try the following menu items. The chicken and waffles on the menu stated chicken breast but we received chicken wings with no explanation. Chicken breast vs. chicken wing equals two different experiences when I want to enjoy them with my waffles. It would have been nice to receive a disclaimer that there was a change before bringing the dish to the table. The breakfast sandwich was small. Yes, it’s packed with   meats, an egg, and a fried green tomato. The fried green tomato was the best part. I may just order the fried green tomatoes by itself next time.
niceee
Amazing!! The food and drinks were absolutely amazing. Get the wings!! Pictured is the Creole penne packed with flavor you will not be disappointed!
I had the chicken and waffles. EXCELLENT!!! Food came out HOT,  and chicken was cooked to perfection. Kudos!!! 3 large pieces,  a wing, drumstick and breast. A real deal

I'd never been to any of these restaurants in the chain before, but several of my friends have and said great things. The ambience was really cute, the food was extremely tasty, and the service was very nice. I got some blueberry mixed drink, crab dip for appetizer, and the bayou penne entree. Sooo much food I had enough to fill me up on leftovers. Good for friends or even dates.
As usual, the atmosphere was sophisticated, relaxed and the food PHENOMENAL!!  Fried green tomatoes with lump crab.....HEAVEN!!!
Delicious food and very nice staff! Thank you!
Great ambience, food, and all the music from our early teen anxiety phase. I loved it!
Unimpressed

Ian truly disappointed I have been here before covid and got the rock fish which was amazing and I had the best customer service I had had in a long tome along with awesome cocktails. I chose to go here on Valentine’s Day and honestly I wish I would’ve just dope dashed something . I ordered the filet Oscar which comes with asparagus and roasted potatoes nothing absolutely nothing even had salt on it the potatoes where so dry they looked dehydrated my steak was cooked properly but had absolutely no seasoning even the holiday  sauce was bland my fiancé ordered the scallop and shrimp risotto it was so under cooked she couldn’t eat it but the shrimp and scallops which was only two each and one of the scallops was raw in the middle . My two glasses of Hennessy and ginger ale probably contained a total Of one shot of alcohol between the two and my poor waitress I believe she must have been very new she couldn’t keep Up with the tables 150$ down the drain and my Valentine’s Day seems incomplete because of the way to have to plan now we can’t just go somewhere else it’s sad but I will never return

We went last night for dinner and although the food was tasty, the time we waited was insane. Our reservation was at 7:30 and we didn’t have our appetizer until 9:00. They must be understaffed during covid. We were comped our appetizer but definitely wish we had better service. Atmosphere is okay, it wasn’t quite the romantic Valentine’s Day vibes I was hoping for. The one in Alexandria, VA is much nicer, but I guess it’s because this is Baltimore.
Service was pleasant and persistent..
Drinks were over priced but food and overall was great and service was excellent! Will recommend...
Very uppity, high priced, but with food that didn’t match. Portions were tiny. Presentation was a little sloppy.
Ended up here accidentally, had an amazing night. Great staff, great food, amazing atmosphere. Will definitely make a stop here each time I'm visiting baltimore!

Amazing restaurant! All the food was delicious. I got the Trident Broiler and my friends got the Shrimp and Grits, 10 oz steak, and sea bass. Portions were generous and nicely laid out on the plate. The crab cake from the Trident Broiler was especially tasty and the grits are the most creamy and buttery grits I've ever had. My nephew got the pepperoni pizza with fries from the kid's menu and that was also really good. Our waiter Tyler was very amicable and invested, making for a smooth and flawless experience! In addition, the restaurant has a very cozy setting.
Excelente service, nice place, good atmosphere and great food. I had a very well cooked sea bas with crab, good job chef
Very nice atmosphere, great cocktails, delicious food, fast service!
Our server was great ( Isiah ) and the food was delicious.  The seasonal cocktail ( spare me the time ) sooo Good.  Tacos are Life--!!
Very very good food and great service
Great staff.  Food was wonderful will def visit again.
Blackwall Hitch is one of my favorite restaurants in the city for happy hour or a full on dining experience.

Delightful!!!!  Blackwell Hitch is superbly delightful!!!!  The management is very attentive and accommodating.  The wait staff are professional, knowledgeable and highly motivated to provide exceptional service.  The menu is plentious for every palate!  The daily specials are always a hit, however there staple items such as the Blackwall Hitch Burger definitely holds its own!!!  The restaurant is spacious with two floors, three separate break out rooms for small events, business meetings, family gathering and/or the likes.  There are two fully stocked bars one on each floor.  The secound floor boast a brunch style setup just in case you decide to plan and have a buffet style lunch or dinner for guest.  The ambience is warm and inviting, the food is delicious and appealing, the staff is friendly and courteous, the state of cleanliness is amazing.  This is no longer the best kept secret in the Baltimore Inner Harbor...because the secret is now out!  Go now, book for an event, gather for a drink, arrive for fun, stay for laughter, leave full, happy and with a new found friend!  This bar none is my BEST CHOICE restaurant BAR NONE!!!!
Pricey and small portions but very good.

The food was delicious and delivered in a timely fashion. Unfortunately, once we were finished and ready for our check, the waitress disappeared. We had to wait awhile to pay, but other than that, the experience was great!

I had a small gathering for my birthday. Everything was beautiful and perfect. The food was amazing. The green tomatoes and the Rockfish so good!! Our waiter Damian I hope I spelled his name correctly but he was very pleasant. Will return again and try their brunch.

I had a very nice experience here tonight. The wait staff was awesome, we ordered and were served quickly. And the food was really good. Social distancing is enforced and masks are required as well. I will definitely return.
Came here and got caprese salad, super fresh and delicious. Mimosas are delicious, great spot in the inner harbor

Disappointed. Menu looked great but food was just ok. Asked if I could have a sandwich on a wrap instead of a bun but was told no. It was too much to cut up the chicken. Did not receive our appetizer until after we had to flag it down, it came after we ate our meals. Challah buns were very dry. Wish I could have had that wrap! :)

The food was ok. I like that they validate parking.

Ordered the seafood salad to go and the amount of seafood that they gave me for the price was disappointing. The fried tomatoes seem like the batter on the tomatoes on the inside was raw. I was not happy.
Great food

What a great place! The staff is so friendly and helpful. We've been there a bunch of times and the food is always great.  Most recently, we went in with a highly unusual request for a bunch of $10 gift cards that had to be rung up on separate purchases to qualify for a promotion that my credit card was running.  I thought they'd laugh in our face and send us on our way, but they took care of us so we'll and handled the whole thing in stride.  If you dine in, you MUST try the flaming crab dip appetizer. It literally arrives at your table on fire. And the naan bread that's included with it is FANTASTIC!  Other recommendations: the softshell crab sandwich is excellent and the burger is to die for.  Give these guys a shot, they're our favorite place in the area!

The Blackwall shrimp is soooo freaking good!!! The sauce is amazing! I get this during happy hour all the time. It's a little pricey normally but it extremely worth it for happy hour. The crab dip is something else that is amazing!!! I had so of the entrees and they've been good too! The soft shell crab sandwich is pretty good as well.  I was disappointed with the risotto and the crab chicken and something something flat bread. I didn't really like the texture of the risotto it was yellow and treated more like rice, it seemed like it was overcooked.  Most of the staff is nice. This is definitely a happy hour spot for me!

Do not go here if you have a food allergy. Ordered a burger with no mayo due to an egg allergy. The burger  came out with mayo 3 times! Not sure if it was the same burger they tried to wipe the mayo off. The manager however was very professional & apologetic.

First time at this establishment.  Heard great things about the Annapolis location and decided to try the one in Baltimore.  I had disappointing interactions with the hostess and the manager, which I will chalk up to the heat as it was nearly 100 degrees that day and because of mandated outdoor seating, we were all slowly baking.  Additionally,  I'm noticing that Covid has negatively affected customer service at restaurants in general.  However, my server, Elias, was very pleasant, accommodating, and made great suggestions.  My party ended up leaving before our meal was served.   Therefore, I cannot review the food. Will not return to this location but, would still like to visit Annapolis.  If you choose to visit this location, I would suggest you wait until indoor dining resumes as the restaurant has no naturally provided shade and the umbrellas and tables cannot be moved so you'll still end up in the sun on a hot day.

Server was nice, family friendly and food was great.
Great food, good live music, and good service.  Can't ask for much more from a restaurant.

Beautiful restaurant, friendly staff, great location.  The signature burger was huge.  My Shobb salad was tasty and the portion of all the salads were generous.  The calamari and crab dip were very good; however, the flat breads are the size of an appetizer...almost laughable.  As a matter of fact, I did laugh because it wasn't mine.

Some friends and I decided to meet at Black Wall Hitch downtown for happy hour. My friends arrived before me and I got there just before happy hour ended. As expected it was busy and there were 2 bartenders at the Bar. I tried Dior about 5 minutes to get their attention. The male bartender ended up walking from behind the bar to attend to tables the female bartender who I now know as Rebecca didn't look our way for while but eventually came over. When she arrived I told her I knew it was after 7 but I had been trying to get her attention for a while so I'd like to still order at Happy Hour prices. Her response well I can get you a drink because that's my bad but I can't do anything about the food. I promptly asked for a manager and she responded " Yea I got a lot going on" she proceeded to go back to the other side of the bar . She alerted the manager I believe his name was James who came over apologized and said he would honor the prices.  There were 2 other woman sitting in the side of me they heard the interaction and said their experience was the same TERRIBLE. She was not attentive and wasn't particularly friendly. My friends who had gotten their before me shared the same sentiment. Now I don't want to make this racial but what I will say she appeared to be super friendly and attentive to the folks at the bar that were facing the center none of whom were people of color. Everyone who was sitting at the end of the bar was women of color.  Just think that should be noted. The food came out it was ok nothing to memorable but not terrible enough to send back. I had wings, saffron mussels, and fried green tomatoes ( those were actually good). James the manager was bright spot super friendly and I think he did a decent job of trying to make things better. However Rebecca needs to work on her attitude and attentiveness. I can't remember the last time I was so offended that I didn't tip. But this time I certainly won't forget.
Great
Excellent food and service.

I came on a Sunday for the brunch buffet ($39.99) with a group of friends (4 in total). To start the decor when you walk in is great.  The hostesses were welcoming and friendly. We had a reservation from opentable so we were seated right away.  They had a jazz band playing and this added to a relaxed yet exciting brunch day.  They have $2 mimosas for brunch. However they are premade and taste like a pure glass of OJ. So we decided to purchase a bottle of prosecco instead with a miniature carafe of OJ. Our server was great btw.  Here is the downside in addition to the mimosas.  The food is hit or miss.  Bacon- not cooked and full of fat. Fried chicken was very good. Grits were the bomb. Seafood omelet underwhelming. Steamed shrimp overcooked. Oysters were good. Potatoes(home fries) were tasteless and cold. Beef was extremely rare and fatty. Sausage patties were yummy. Salmon... what salmon? They never refilled it. The tongs to pick up the food were adult proof. Very difficult to use.  After we ate we ordered a bloody Mary.  Nothing worth remembering.  Overall I am glad I came. The location is prime and great for a walk on the harbor after eating.  I don't think the food was worth the price paid but it wasn't aweful.  Food 2.5* Service 4.5* Ambiance 5* Drinks 2.5*  So my overall rating is 3.6*  It's a great 1st time experience.  However I don't know that I would come back. Well definitely not for brunch.
The food was delicious but I think the food is overpriced. The waiter was very nice.

Delicious brunch, terrible set-up. During a previous visit , the buffet was in the back room ( which was great) today, it was along the windows.  The buffet line was extremely long as if they were herding goat; the omelette guy was making one at a time.  I’m not sure why the set-up of the buffet change but it was a horrible experience.

Food was great service was remarkably terrible.  A server should not scold a customer for the actions of his coworker. It set a really bad tone for the dinner. Service never improved as the waiter continued to disregard me at my table of 11.
awesome food!

First time visiting this location, its brand new and has a great vibe. I only drank but I did look at the food menu and I suspect it's probably a bit over priced to the area, although it is surrounded by tourist trap locations so perhaps it'll get by okay.

Restaurant week is just as great coming here and the Catfish is to die for. I need seconds already and I just got it last night. We used the private event room upstairs for a business dinner. It was perfect. The service was excellent, food good, and everything went smoothly. I would highly recommend for other business related private events.

Attended a birthday party here for a dear friend on a Saturday evening. The ambiance was great, the food and service were top notch, and the drinks were amazing. You must try the Strawberry Jalapeno Mojito! It is their signature drink. Lovely view of the Inner Harbor and valet parking is available. Nice for a romantic date night or to hang out with friends. There is an upstairs and a downstairs option for seating.

While I can only address their happy hour and not a traditional dining experience, I highly recommend eating and drinking here! Their HH prices and selection is great (FYI - you have to dine in the bar area to take advantage of their HH) as was the service and people watching. Everything we ordered tasted great (strawberry & goat cheese flatbread, cheeseburger sliders, wings, fried green tomatoes, and oysters) and was very reasonably priced. We were only in town two nights and my husband wanted to come back for round 2!

My wife and I were in Baltimore passing through for the first day of our honeymoon. We stopped here for dinner around 4:15PM. First off, the atmosphere seemed great, very comfortable, not too loud and some nice decoration. The waiter we got was attentive and helpful, fully explained specials, drink options, etc. Now we are from Buffalo, NY, so when I saw chicken wings for an appetizer, I thought we would try something from another area. We ordered the Sweet-chili BBQ Garlic wings... an interesting combination. They arrived quickly and they were THE ABSOLUTE BEST WINGS WE HAVE BOTH EVER HAD. We told the waiter right away who clearly passes the word on to the manager as he came over to us to talk. I explained how incredible they were and told him to pass my compliments to the chef. Not only did he do that, he brought the chef out to talk to us; it's great to see he was truly getting recognition for what he made. In passing, my wife mentioned how this was our first day married and that he helped make it a great day. I ordered a burger which was spectacular, and she a Southwest chicken salad which she fully enjoyed as well. While we were eating, the chef himself came out with a dessert for each of us, and wrote congrats on the plate; and of course it was on the house. He wished us well on our marriage and was incredibly respectful and kind. This is the kind of restaurant I will recommend to anyone and everyone. I will be back here the next time I'm remotely near Baltimore. This was an A++.
